.TH "__tcs_buffer_write" 9 "__tcs_buffer_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__tcs_buffer_write \- Write to TCS hardware from a request; don't trigger.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __tcs_buffer_write
.BI "(struct rsc_drv *drv "  ","
.BI "int tcs_id "  ","
.BI "int cmd_id "  ","
.BI "const struct tcs_request *msg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drv" 12
The controller.
.IP "tcs_id" 12
The global ID of this TCS.
.IP "cmd_id" 12
The index within the TCS to start writing.
.IP "msg" 12
The message we want to send, which will contain several addr/data
pairs to program (but few enough that they all fit in one TCS).
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is used for all types of transfers (active, sleep, and wake).
